&quot;Edgard Victor Achille Charles Varèse (French: [ɛdɡaːʁ viktɔːʁ aʃil ʃaʁl vaʁɛːz]; also spelled Edgar Varèse; December 22, 1883 – November 6, 1965) was an innovative French-born composer who spent the greater part of his career in the United States.&quot;
<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edgard_Var%c3%a8se" rel="nofollow">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edgard_Var%C3%A8se</a>

In February 1919 (date on negative: 2-25-19) the  <a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn83030214/1919-02-23/ed-1/seq-65/" rel="nofollow">New-York tribune., February 23, 1919, Page 11 </a>, col. 4 reported that he was conductor of a new symphony orchestra. See also <a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn83030193/1919-04-12/ed-1/seq-7/" rel="nofollow"> The evening world., April 12, 1919, Final Edition, Page 7, col. 5</a> &quot;Edgar Varese Starts His New Symphony Band&quot;.
